observations.recommendation:
The Audit Team recommended that the LCE:
instruct the Inventory Committee to prioritize the conduct of a thorough and complete physical inventory and reconcile the results thereon with the accounting records to ascertain the accuracy, completeness and existence of the reported PPE in the financial statement;
instruct the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO with complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects, to facilitate the preparation of Local Road Inventory and Road Map and aids in the conduct of physical inventory on road network projects;
instruct the Municipal Accountant and Inventory Committee to reclassify the properties costing below P50,000.00 to semi-expendable properties and make the necessary reclassification of PPE accounts considering the hereunder adjusting journal entries to present the correct balances of the affected accounts in the FS; and
instruct the Property Officer, the Head of Inventory Committee and the Municipal Accountant to adhere with the guidelines and procedures set forth under COA Circular 2020-06 dated January 31, 2020 for the conduct of physical count of properties; recognition of PPE items found at station; disposition for non-existing/missing PPE items; and for the one-time cleansing of PPE account balances, to reflect more reliable and accurate balances of PPE accounts in the FS, hence to convey precise information useful in decision making and accountability for these properties.

The Audit Team recommended that the LCE instruct the Municipal Engineer to abide strictly with the provisions of COA Circular No. 2013-004 by:
ensuring that all PPAs are included or reported in the Quarterly Report of PPAs to facilitate monitoring and inspection by the Audit Team;
posting of the signboards/billboards containing all the relevant information pertaining to the project at hand at the project site to enable to inform the public of the endeavors of the Municipality to encourage public participation which in turn promotes good governance through transparency;
submitting at the beginning of the year a list of all on-going government PPAs and those that are to be implemented during the year to the Audit Team for monitoring purposes; and
informing the Audit Team within ten days after the award of the infrastructure project or before the start of the program/activity that the appropriate project signboards and/or public notices are already posted for verification.

We recommended that LCE require:
1. the Municipal Engineer and the Acting MPDC to strictly monitor the accomplishment of the contractors as reflected in the SWA submitted;
2. the Municipal Engineer to review the accuracy or propriety of the contract duration being programmed for the need to decrease the same since the contractor could accomplish such project for a shorter period of time to avoid wastage of government funds;
3. the Municipal Engineer to remind the contractors to strictly follow the terms and conditions provided in the Bid Documents specifically the Instruction to Bidders, Special Conditions of the Contract, General Conditions, Perfected Contract and that the authority to commence the awarded infrastructure projects after the successful completion of the bidding process is only upon the receipt of the Notice to Proceed; the foregoing ensure compliance with the provisions of RA 9184 and delivery of quality infrastructure projects.

